    "While the goal of this hypothesis is to seek and then explain how a second language is acquired.",
    "In its most fundamental form, the input hypothesis argues that learners progress along the natural order only",
    "Theory in Second Language Acquisition (Recognition of Concepts Toward Krashen's Second Language Acquisition Theory for Five Main Hypotheses), Pauzan 20884",
    "when they encounter second language input that is one step ahead of their position in the natural order.",
